-- MOVES-Tatsuya Kamoi joins Mercer to lead the far east market
-- 
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 02:09AM EDT
-- None



Aug 6 (Reuters) - Mercer, a subsidiary of Marsh & McLennan Co <MMC.N>, named Tatsuya Kamoi as market leader for the far east market.

Kamoi will be based in Tokyo and will report to Gaurav Garg, regional president of growth markets, Mercer. Kamoi will serve as a member of the Growth Markets Regional Leadership Team. Prior to Mercer, Kamoi was vice president of industrial services business at International Business Machine Corp's <IBM.N> Japan unit.